nsidering dynamic class loading**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether dynamic class loading is really necessary here. It seems like it could be okay without it. I wonder if there's a need for a dependency on the TCK, or if the plugin might provide that instead. I'm curious about existing tests to see if they use it or not. It feels like there's quite a bit to unpack, so I'll need to search for more information.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_To1Hl6rK1g1qnyqyFWz1PqOv|fc_0fb42abf585d89e00169f53d2acd74819eb9e0ed72ed2bb686", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"NativeImageSupport\" tests/src -n | head -50", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4042, "output": 2077, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32231, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777679627779, "responseId": "resp_0fb42abf585d89e00169f53d0c3bd4819e974cf610c1c4f651"}}
